Steve Martin as **Enneagram Type 5w4** (self-preservation), "Comedy's Analytical Recluse." The thesis: the flailing "wild and crazy guy" wasn't the opposite of the analytical man, it was his *product* — an anxious introvert who engineered laughter like a physics problem, performed through two decades of private panic attacks, mastered stand-up and abandoned it whole at the peak, and spent fifty years chasing the approval of a father who reviewed his breakout with "Well, he's no Charlie Chaplin."

